Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 16:33:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 22/37] web-app: message info shows attachment details and
 failure reason
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Extend the Message Info dialog (BasicMessageInfo) with an attachment
section — file name, MIME type, size, image/video dimensions and
audio/video duration — shown only for messages that carry a file.

Also surface delivery failures directly in this dialog: a prominent
error banner is rendered when the message is in the OUT_FAILED state (or
carries an error string). The failed-status icon in the message bubble
now opens the Message Info dialog instead of a bare alert, so the
failure reason has a clear, consistent home alongside the other
delivery metadata.

Adds the untranslated labels Type/Size/Resolution/Duration.
